div.p: url-shortener-m5 gateway/circuitbreaker/circuitbreaker.go Mutex (mu sync.Mutex) held on ALL state reads/writes except State() (atomic)

Legend CLOSED normal traffic flow OPEN fast-fail; 503 returned immediately HALF_OPEN single probe allowed; all others 503 Failure definition: HTTP 5xx from downstream OR connection refused / timeout (30 s) Mutex: mu sync.Mutex acquired in Allow(), RecordSuccess(), RecordFailure() Atomic read: State() uses atomic.LoadInt32 (no mutex needed for observability-only reads) Config (DefaultConfig): FailureThreshold = 5 consecutive failures Window = 10 s observation period OpenDuration = 30 s before probe allowed

ul.li: probeInFlight == false Fields (live) state State = 0 (Closed) failureCount int [0,5) lastFailureAt time.Time openedAt time.Time // zero probeInFlight bool = false Allow() (true, nil) always permits; resets count on RecordSuccess

probeInFlight == false Fields (live) state State = 1 (Open) failureCount int = 0 lastFailureAt time.Time openedAt time.Time // set on trip probeInFlight bool = false Allow() (false, ErrCircuitOpen) until time.Since(openedAt) >= 30s

probeInFlight {true, false} Fields (live) state State = 2 (HalfOpen) failureCount int = 0 lastFailureAt time.Time openedAt time.Time // retained probeInFlight bool // true = probe active Allow() probe slot: !probeInFlight set true, return (true, nil) probeInFlight return (false, ErrCircuitOpen)
